1.title: Omaha
1.plot: One year after losing the presidency, Selina attempts to secure her legacy, Dan tries to ingratiate himself at his new job, while Amy's brash D.C.-style personality proves too much for her new co-workers.

2.title: Library
2.plot: A visit to former President Hughes' library sparks Selina's imagination, Jonah gets advice on how to rise in the political ranks, Dan experiences friction at work, and Amy tries to adjust to her new role.

3.title: Georgia
3.plot: Selina and her team travel to Georgia to oversee the country's first free democratic election.

4.title: Justice
4.plot: Selina and her team attend the funeral of a Supreme Court Justice, Amy works on securing a location for Selina's library, while Dan tries to maintain his upswing with his co-host.

5.title: Chicklet
5.plot: Having settled on a location for her presidential library, Selina and Mike get to work on her book. Meanwhile, Dan lands in a gossip column.

6.title: Qatar
6.plot: Selena travels to Qatar and finds an opportunity to redeem her past blunders, Jonah has a productive dinner with an old foe, while Dan receives an unexpected visit.

7.title: Blurb
7.plot: While her staff prepares for her portrait unveiling, Selina and Mike try to finish her book.

8.title: Judge
8.plot: Selina and her team travel south for Gary's 40th birthday party, Dan is forced to arrange an interview with Jonah, while Mike's incompetence sends him and Amy on a wild goose chase.

9.title: A Woman First
9.plot: Selina's book finally arrives, but her legacy is almost immediately under threat due to the publication of Mike's diary, while both Dan and Jonah experience troubles of their own.

10.title: Groundbreaking
10.plot: Selina and her team prepare for the long awaited opening of her library, which is unsurprisingly beset by complications.

1.title: Fundraiser
1.plot: Vice President Selina Meyer and her staff - chief of staff Amy, spokesperson Mike, right-hand man Gary, and executive assistant Sue - are still finding their footing in Washington D.C. Selina decides to make the Clean Jobs Commission a pet project, but a series of missteps requires her staff to work damage control.

2.title: Frozen Yoghurt
2.plot: The Veep's office is revived by good news that her task force is likely to be green lit. With the President (conveniently) out of the country, Selina looks to make headway on filibuster reform and meeting with some 'normal' people.

3.title: Catherine
3.plot: Faced with a trumped-up story of a rift between the Veep and the First Lady, Selina quells accusations that everything is about her--even though it is. Gary selects candidates for the VP dog, though Selina's daughter Catherine gets final say.

4.title: Chung
4.plot: Dan and Amy attend a book launch for Gov. Danny Chung, a charismatic Asian-American war hero, who Selina worries could be a political threat. Meanwhile, Selina preps with Mike for a 'Meet the Press' interview.

5.title: Nicknames
5.plot: Selina becomes obsessed with the (many) unflattering nicknames given to her by bloggers, and after a snub, assigns Dan to get White House intel from Jonah. Later, Dan's political maneuvering puts the fate of the Clean Jobs bill on the line.

6.title: Baseball
6.plot: Selina attends a healthy-eating event at Camden Yards with some grumpy fast-food executives, where she also confides a secret to Amy. Mike holds a press briefing for some local news pals. Amy and Dan are forced to entertain elementary-school children.

7.title: Full Disclosure
7.plot: With the Veep and her staff taking flack over a pregnancy rumor and the firing of a Secret Service agent, Selina orders a 'partial' full disclosure of all office correspondence and threatens to fire a key staffer.

8.title: Tears
8.plot: Season One Finale. Selina travels to Ohio to support a gubernatorial candidate who no longer wants her endorsement; the Clean Jobs bill comes back to haunt Dan; Mike and Amy open the floodgates after they play up Selina's tears.

1.title: Midterms
1.plot: Season Two Premiere. Fresh off successful campaign appearances for midterm elections, Selina sees an opportunity to expand her role, but must first curry favor with the president's icy senior strategist Kent Davison (Gary Cole). Meanwhile, the staff's personal lives have some new developments.

2.title: Signals
2.plot: Selina attends a pig roast in North Carolina as part of the president's 'Listen to Rural America' initiative. Dan takes up Pilates to get face time.

3.title: Hostages
3.plot: As a hostage crisis in Uzbekistan heats up, Selina and Secretary of Defense General Maddox have trouble getting on the same page at their joint appearance at the Marine Corps Base at Quantico. Sue testifies at a Congressional hearing on governmental efficiencies; Dan and Gary jockey for the Veep's ear.

4.title: The Vic Allen Dinner
4.plot: Selina is rankled when the White House releases an unflattering photo of her. Mike and Kent bond over sailing; Jonah gets an executive parking space; Sue has a job interview. Selina takes steps to keep her staff happy as they prepare for her appearance at the Vic Allen dinner.

5.title: Helsinki
5.plot: Selina and her staff head to Helsinki to finalize a trade agreement, but are worried whether Selina will be received warmly in Europe. Dan calls Mike for advice on charming the press and Mike leans on Jonah for help. Kent and Ben argue over how to deal with new intel.

6.title: Andrew
6.plot: After an allergic reaction shuts down her budget negotiation with Majority Leader Mary King, Selina moves the talks to Catherine's 21st birthday bash. Meanwhile, Amy and Gary fret over how Selina will handle seeing her ex-husband Andrew at the party; Mike fields press inquiries on Selina's role in the Uzbek hostage crisis.

7.title: Shutdown
7.plot: With D.C. in the midst of a government shutdown, Selina is forced to furlough some of her staff. A damaging story leaks about Selina's ex-husband Andrew; Danny Chung takes advantage of the shutdown; Gary and Jonah go on a run to retrieve Selina's trash.

8.title: First Response
8.plot: After being prepped for a 'puff piece' interview at the VP residence, Selina is thrown by Janet Ryland's 'gotcha' questions.

9.title: Running
9.plot: Undeterred by a message that POTUS wants Selina to limit her public appearances, the Veep continues her plans. Dan attempts to play both sides of the Selina/Danny Chung rivalry.

10.title: D.C.
10.plot: (Season Two Finale) With the administration in full crisis mode and Selina's future in doubt, the entire staff goes on frenzied job hunt.

1.title: Some New Beginnings
1.plot: During her book signing tour for her new autobiography "Some New Beginnings," Selena receives some interesting news. Meanwhile, Mike is getting married, and Amy and Dan fight over a coveted promotion.

2.title: The Choice
2.plot: Following POTUS' new stance on abortion, Selina is forced to reconsider hers. Jonah starts a consulting firm outlet called Ryantology. Kent flirts with Sue.

3.title: Alicia
3.plot: While Selina and her staff prepare for an Annapolis event where she will announce her candidacy, Dan gets word that SNL has done a not-so-flattering sketch on the Veep.

4.title: Clovis
4.plot: On a fundraising trip in Silicon Valley, Selina is challenged by an anti-fracking mom and visits the campus of Clovis, a tech company with a young, ambitious CEO. Back in D.C., Jonah makes a crude viral video of the Selina/mom encounter, and Dan, with Ben's help, gets an idea for a rumor he can spread against Chung.

5.title: Fishing
5.plot: As Amy and Dan vie for position as Selina's campaign manager, Ben arranges a secret lunch for the Veep with hotshot strategist Bill Ericsson. Meanwhile, Mike tries to maintain his strict fertility schedule; Jonah is offered a job on Maddox's team; and Gary's mysterious shoulder pain threatens his job. Later, Selina is invited by Maddox to his country house, and Amy has a dinner party with the staff as part of her pitch.

6.title: Detroit
6.plot: At an economic summit in Detroit, Selina's staff and her family are peeved by the presence of her new personal trainer, Ray. Meanwhile, Jonah and Mike negotiate a photo-op with Selina and Maddox. Later, Catherine protects her mom from a protestor, and Selina attends a women's gun show.

7.title: Special Relationship
7.plot: Crossover episode with Armando Iannucci's previous political sitcom The Thick of It.

8.title: Debate
8.plot: Selina and the staff prep for her debate with Maddox, Chung, Congressman Owen Pierce, and Joe Thornhill--a major-league baseball manager who has recently entered the race. Dan returns with a rosier outlook; Mike's wife Wendy arrives to do a style piece on Selina, but eyes a bigger story involving Ray.

9.title: Crate
9.plot: With Thornhill ahead in the polls, Selina and her staff discuss how to make her more folksy. Jonah, in need of a job, meets with Bill Ericsson, and asks his mom to reach out to his influential uncle Jeff. Selina has an interview with a pretentious journalist named Quincy Carter.

10.title: New Hampshire
10.plot: Season Three Finale. Three days before the New Hampshire primary, Selina and her staff juggle her multiple official obligations and campaign appearances.

1.title: Joint Session
1.plot: Selina's staff frantically works on her first major speech as president; Gary questions his worth.

2.title: East Wing
2.plot: The President's staff prepares for her state visit with the Israeli Prime Minister.

3.title: Data
3.plot: Selina's team tries to find a scapegoat; Catherine wants to support an anti-bullying campaign.

4.title: Tehran
4.plot: President Meyer travels to Iran, where an American reporter is being detained.

5.title: Convention
5.plot: Selina and her staff scramble to avert a major internal crisis; Amy is angry with a new advisor.

6.title: Storms and Pancakes
6.plot: Selina is annoyed by the press' reaction to her running mate's charm.

7.title: Mommy Meyer
7.plot: The President is shaken by a dramatic incident at the White House.

8.title: B/ill
8.plot: Gary sets up a secret meeting with Dan and Amy to persuade them to lobby against Selina's bill.

9.title: Testimony
9.plot: Members of Selina's staff testify before a congressional committee.

10.title: Election Night
10.plot: Selina and her staff find their nerves growing frayed as each state result is called.

1.title: Morning After
1.plot: On the day after the election, Selina sees a possible road to victory, Senator James gets a new role, Mike prepares for a new addition to his family, and Dan considers his career options.

2.title: Nev-AD-a
2.plot: While Amy, Dan, Jonah and Richard lead the Nevada recount effort, Mike begins a new diet, Kent tries to figure out how old Sue is, and Selina meets a billionaire banker.

3.title: The Eagle
3.plot: A sensitive tweet posted accidentally by Selina causes chaos for the team.

4.title: Mother
4.plot: Selina is forced to put her campaign on hold when her mother suffers a stroke.

5.title: Thanksgiving
5.plot: As Thanksgiving arrives, a new crisis hits the team, with Selina left unable to fulfill her duties. Meanwhile, Dan takes on a new role, and Jonah receives exciting news.

6.title: C**tgate
6.plot: As the country faces a massive financial crisis, Selina must make an important decision. Meanwhile, Jonah campaigns in New Hampshire and Amy is asked to find the source of disparaging comments made about Selina.

7.title: Congressional Ball
7.plot: Selina's plan to lobby votes at the annual White House Congressional Ball goes awry, while Dan tries to save Jonah's disastrous campaign.

8.title: Camp David
8.plot: Selina takes Catherine to Camp David, ostensibly for a family Christmas celebration, but also to conduct secret talks with the Chinese government. Meanwhile, Amy and Dan try to help Jonah win as his election campaign reaches its conclusion.

9.title: Kissing Your Sister
9.plot: As Catherine's documentary is completed, Congress decides who will be President.

10.title: Inauguration
10.plot: Selina and her staff prepare for inauguration day.

imdb.plot outline: "Politics is about people," former Sen. Selina Meyer is fond of saying. Unfortunately, the people Meyer, a charismatic leader and rising star in her party, meets after becoming vice president are nothing like she expected, but everything she was warned about. "Veep" follows the new VP as she puts out political fires, juggles her public schedule and private life, and does everything within her limited powers to improve her dysfunctional relationship with the chief executive. Meyer's trusted -- and some not-so-trusted -- aides include chief of staff Amy, spokesperson Mike, secretary Sue and right-hand man Gary.
imdb.title: Veep
plot: Former Senator Selina Meyer finds that being Vice President of the United States is nothing like she hoped and everything that everyone ever warned her about.::Anonymous

"Politics is about people," former Sen. Selina Meyer is fond of saying. Unfortunately, the people Meyer, a charismatic leader and rising star in her party, meets after becoming vice president are nothing like she expected, but everything she was warned about. "_Veep_ (qv)" follows the new VP as she puts out political fires, juggles her public schedule and private life, and does everything within her limited powers to improve her dysfunctional relationship with the chief executive. Meyer's trusted -- and some not-so-trusted -- aides include chief of staff Amy, spokesperson Mike, secretary Sue and right-hand man Gary.::Jwelch5742

Former Senator Selina Meyer has accepted the call to serve as Vice President of the United States. The job is nothing like she imagined and everything she was warned about. '_Veep_ (qv)' follows Meyer and her staff as they attempt to make their mark and leave a lasting legacy, without getting tripped up in the day-to-day political games that define Washington.::HBO
